# Research sample-workspace JSON (tsconfig.json, nx.json, turbo.json,
# project.json, …) is kept in the `pretty-format-json` pre-commit hook's
# canonical form (sorted keys, one array element per line). Prettier formats
# JSON arrays the opposite way (collapsed), so the two hooks would fight on
# every commit. Exclude these sample JSON from Prettier and let
# pretty-format-json own them. `package.json` is negated back in: the
# pretty-format-json hook ignores it, so Prettier keeps managing it.
docs/research/monorepo-tooling/*/sample/**/*.json
!docs/research/monorepo-tooling/*/sample/**/package.json
